    <sharedstimuli>
        <sharedstimulus id="assets/d67a0fbc638545fa51830/passage NEW.xml">
            <label key="90146b8f4c6eb5e1c3bb64e643cacda4">
                <text>Earthquakes</text>
            </label>
            <label key="c8e20cbc488308eda848d234fb5fe90e">
                <text>An earthquake is the passage of seismic waves through an environment when energy is released from within Earth’s crust.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="58fd70a330e8170d52b849f07870eaa2">
                <text>The point where an earthquake originates is called the hypocentre. The point on Earth’s surface directly above a hypocentre is called the epicentre. </text>
            </label>
            <label key="e84455a89a40947b2ecb2df18c1a3bb5">
                <text>The epicentre<em></em>is where the greatest intensity from an earthquake is felt.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="eb31c1853abf876ff04ad1b52f42a8f0">
                <text>A fault is a fracture or series of fractures between two blocks of rock. </text>
            </label>
            <label key="c268fba781759fac3e7915571c1766cb">
                <text>Earthquake risk is generally high in areas where faults occur.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="6174f1e718692d9e2054dd11f46a8703">
                <text>epicentre</text>
            </label>
            <label key="f69146e7af0c152a790e11fd4847230f">
                <text>hypocentre</text>
            </label>
            <label key="3881bfd1571f85c6562ddfac94ea80ba">
                <text>fault</text>
            </label>
        </sharedstimulus>
    </sharedstimuli>
    <items>
        <item id="i638546cdb361740071ae20415011ec154d">
            <label key="e37ac06b04122d8491350cac5babed8e">
                <text>Are the following statements about earthquakes correct?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="a8c38cd5723dd799a00d4ac84d71561e">
                <text>Select ‘Yes’ or ‘No’ for each statement.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="fdc1563a8afc5411a7aba3beeb918bd4">
                <text>
                    <strong>Yes</strong>
                </text>
            </label>
            <label key="758eaa648d8250f58a4ec4251f2ea215">
                <text>
                    <strong>No</strong>
                </text>
            </label>
            <label key="5a22ee05c832850cc1f25fbebf0f3ba3">
                <text>As the energy of an earthquake increases, the intensity of the earthquake decreases.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="4606aca56b5bc0423921d043c1027908">
                <text>As the distance between the hypocentre and the epicentre increases, the intensity of the earthquake decreases.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="f447713471b83d6d481ef91805c9b902">
                <text>An earthquake’s destructiveness is lower in areas of sandy soil than in areas of granite.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="7334538ce703640c66a02425a913e0bc">
                <text>Earthquakes are often caused by  movements of tectonic plates.</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i638546f06ebfc4007329fdf6e86bf76c02">
